                     1.  MODELS:
In LangChain , "models" are the core interfaces through which you interact with AI models.

NLP ->Chatbot 
2 problems:
NLU(Natural Language Understanding)
reply(Context aware text generation)

Chatbot->LLMS ->internet use->Billions of parameters->huge size(>100GB)

In langchain ..we can communicate with 2 types of AI models:
1.Language model->LLMS :text(input) ->text(output)
2.Embedding model->text(input)->vector(output) [semantic search]

                        2.PROMPTS
Prompts are input provided to a LLM.
    1.Dynamic and reusable prompts
    2.Role-based prompts
    3.Few shot prompting

                         3.CHAINS
we can build pipelines with the help of chains.
output of previous stage automatically becomes input of next stage. 

             Complex pipelines:
1.Parallel chains
2.Conditional chains

                       4.INDEXES
Indexes connect your application to external knowledge-such as PDFs, websites or databases.
1.Doc loader
2.text splitter
3.vector store
4.Retrievers 

                      5.MEMORY
LLM API calls are stateless. 
1.Conversation Buffer Memory:
Stores a transcript of recent messages.Great for short chats but can grow large quickly.
2.Conversation Buffer Window memory:
Only keeps the last N interactions to avoid excessive token usage.
3.Summarizer-Based-Memory : 
Periodically summarizes older chat segments to keep a condesed memory footprint.
4.Custom Memory: For advanced use cases, you can stoe specialized state
(e.g. the user's preferances or key facts about them) in a custom memory class.


